content.text: table is designed to store detailed financial and usage data related to utility billing for various agencies and facilities. It captures both original and revised billing amounts, energy usage, and demand metrics on a monthly basis, along with fiscal year-to-date summaries. The table also tracks changes in these metrics and whether the readings are actual or estimated. This structure supports detailed financial analysis and reporting for utility management.

The complexity of this table is high due to its extensive number of columns, the use of default functions, and the detailed financial and usage tracking across multiple dimensions (monthly, fiscal year-to-date, original vs. revised). The presence of numerous default functions and the potential for complex business logic further contribute to its complexity.

Supporting audits and reconciliations of utility bills by comparing original and revised billing data.
Facilitating budget planning and forecasting based on historical utility data.
